The FAA is considering an amendment to part 71 of the Federal Aviation Regulations (14 CFR part 71) to amend Class E airspace
at Nashville International Airport, Tennessee. Runways 2C and 20C have been extended. The Class E airspace extending
upward from 700 feet above the surface is proposed to be extended from a 10-mile radius to a 15-mile radius of the Nashville
