<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
cargo across a surface with none of the weight of the cargo 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
supported by the fall. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
designated person
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a person who 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
possesses specialized abilities in a specific area and is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
assigned by the employer to perform a specific task in the area. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
dockboards (car and bridge plates)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 mean 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
devices for spanning short distances between, for example, two 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
barges, which do not expose employees to falls greater than 4 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
feet (1.2 m). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
employee
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means any longshore worker, or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
other person engaged in longshoring operations or related 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employments other than the master, ship's officers, crew of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
vessel, or any person engaged by the master to load or unload any 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
vessel under 18 net tons. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
employer
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a person or company that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employs workers in longshoring operations or related employments, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as defined herein. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
enclosed space
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means an interior space in or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
on a vessel, other than a confined space, that may contain or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accumulate a hazardous atmosphere due to inadequate natural 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ventilation. Examples of enclosed spaces are holds, deep tanks 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and refrigerated compartments. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fumigant
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 is a substance or mixture of substances, used 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to kill pests or prevent infestation, which is a gas or is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rapidly or progressively transformed to the gaseous state, even 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
though some nongaseous or particulate matter may remain and be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
dispersed in the treatment space. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
gangway
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means any ramp-like or stair-like 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
means of access provided to enable personnel to board or leave a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
vessel, including accommodation ladders, gangplanks and brows. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(j) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
hazardous cargo, materials, substance or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
atmosphere
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Any substance listed in 29 CFR part 1910, subpart Z; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Any material in the Hazardous Materials Table and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Hazardous Materials Communications Regulations of the Department 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of Transportation, 49 CFR part 172; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Any article not properly described by a name in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Hazardous Materials Table and Hazardous Materials Communication 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Regulations of the Department of Transportation, 49 CFR part 172, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
but which is properly classified under the definitions of those 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
categories of dangerous articles given in 49 CFR part 173; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Any atmosphere with an oxygen content of less than 19.5 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
percent or greater than 23 percent. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(k) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
intermodal container
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a reusable cargo 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
container of rigid construction and rectangular configuration; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fitted with devices permitting its ready handling, particularly 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
its transfer from one mode of transport to another; so designed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to be readily filled and emptied; intended to contain one or more 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
articles of cargo or bulk commodities for transportation by water 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and one or more other transport modes. The term includes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
completely enclosed units, open top units, fractional height 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
units, units incorporating liquid or gas tanks and other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
variations fitting into the container system. It does not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
include cylinders, drums, crates, cases, cartons, packages, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sacks, unitized loads or any other form of packaging. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(l) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
longshoring operations
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the loading, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
unloading, moving or handling of cargo, ship's stores, gear, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
etc., into, in, on, or out of any vessel. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
