<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(m) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
public vessel
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a vessel owned and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
operated by a government and not regularly employed in merchant 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
service. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(n) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
ramp
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means other flat surface devices for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
passage between levels and across openings not covered under the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
term ``dockboards''. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(o) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
related employments
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means any employments 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
performed as an incident to or in conjunction with longshoring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
operations, including, but not restricted to, securing cargo, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rigging, and employment as a porter, clerk, checker, or watchman. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(p) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Secretary
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the Secretary of Labor. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(q) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
small trimming hatch
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a small hatch or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
opening, pierced in the 'tween-deck or other intermediate deck of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a vessel, and intended for the trimming of dry bulk cargoes. It 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
does not refer to the large hatchways through which cargo is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
normally handled. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(r) The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
vessel
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 includes every description of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
watercraft or other artificial contrivance used or capable of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
being used as a means of transportation on water, including 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
special purpose floating structures not primarily designed for or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
used as a means of transportation on water. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(s) For the purposes of &sect;&sect;1918.21, 1918.23, 1918.35, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1918.37, and 1918.43(f)(2), the term ``barge'' means an unpowered, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
flatbottomed, shallow draft vessel including river barges, scows, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
carfloats, and lighters. For the purposes of these sections the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
term does not include ship shaped or deep draft barges. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(t) For the purposes of &sect;&sect;1918.21 and 1918.23, the term 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
``river towboat'' means a shallow draft, low freeboard, self 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
propelled vessel designed to tow river barges by pushing ahead. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
For purposes of these sections the term does not include other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
towing vessels. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(u) For the purpose of &sect;1918.11, the term ``vessel's cargo 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
handling gear'' includes that gear which is a permanent part of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the vessel's equipment and which is used for the handling of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
cargo other than bulk liquids. It does not include gear which is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
used only for handling or holding hoses, handling ship's stores 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or handling the gangway, or boom conveyor belt systems for the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
self-unloading of bulk cargo vessels. It does include all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
stationary or mobile cargo handling appliances, including shore-based power-operated ramps, used on shore or on
board ship for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
suspending, raising, or lowering loads or moving them from one 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
position to another while suspended or supported. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) For the purpose of &sect;1918.23(b), the term ``Mississippi 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
River System'' includes the Mississippi River from the head of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
navigation to its mouth, and navigable tributaries including the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Illinois Waterway, Missouri River, Ohio River, Tennessee River, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Allegheny River, Cumberland River, Green River, Kanawha River, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Monongahela River, and such others to which barge operations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
extend. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

