and valid cargo gear register and certificates which in form and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
content are in substantial accordance with the recommendations of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the International Labor Office, as set forth in Appendix I of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this part, and as provided by International Labor Organization 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Convention No. 152, and which indicates that the cargo gear has 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
been tested, examined and heat treated by or under the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
supervision of persons or organizations defined as competent to 
