to 46 CFR part 91 are deemed to meet the requirements of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
paragraph (a) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) With respect to U.S. vessels not holding a valid 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Certificate of Inspection issued by the U.S. Coast Guard, persons 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or organizations competent to make entries in the registers and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
issue the certificates required by paragraph (a) of this section 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall be only those persons currently accredited by (OSHA) U.S. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Department of Labor, as provided in part 1919 of this chapter. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) With respect to vessels under foreign registry, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
persons or organizations competent to make entries in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
registers and issue the certificates required by paragraph (a) of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this section shall be: 
