<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) The employer shall adhere to the manufacturer's recommended ratings for wire rope and wire rope slings provided
for use aboard ship, and shall have such ratings available for inspection. When the manufacturer is unable to supply
such ratings, the employer shall use tables for wire rope and wire rope slings found in Appendix II to this part. A design
safety factor of at least five shall be maintained for the common sizes of running wire used as falls in purchases, or
in such uses as light load slings. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Wire rope with a safety factor of less than five may be used only as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) In specialized equipment, such as, but not limited to, cranes designed to be used with lesser wire rope safety factors;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) In accordance with design factors in standing rigging applications; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) For heavy lifts or other purposes for which a safety factor of five is not feasible and for which the employer can
demonstrate that equivalent safety is ensured. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Wire rope or wire rope slings provided by the employer and having any of the following conditions shall not be used:

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Ten randomly distributed broken wires in one rope lay or three or more broken wires in one strand in one rope lay;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Kinking, crushing, bird caging or other damage resulting in distortion of the wire rope structure; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Evidence of heat damage; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Excessive wear or corrosion, deformation or other defect in the wire or attachments, including cracks in attachments;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Any indication of strand or wire slippage in end attachments; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) More than one broken wire in the close vicinity of a socket or swaged fitting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Protruding ends of strands in splices on slings and bridles shall be covered or blunted. Coverings shall be removable
so that splices can be examined. Means used to cover or blunt ends shall not damage the wire. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Where wire rope clips are used to form eyes, the employer shall adhere to the manufacturer's recommendations,
which shall be available for inspection. If ``U'' bolt clips are used and the manufacturer's recommendations are
not available, Table 1 of Appendix II to this part shall be used to determine the number and spacing of clips. ``U'' bolts
shall be applied with the ``U'' section in contact with the dead end of the rope. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Wire rope shall not be secured by knotting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Eyes in wire rope bridles, slings, bull wires, or in single parts used for hoisting shall not be formed by wire rope
clips or knots. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) Eye splices in wire ropes shall have at least three tucks with a whole strand of the rope, and two tucks with one-half
of the wire cut from each strand. Other forms of splices or connections which are shown to be equivalently safe may be
used. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) Except for eye splices in the ends of wires and endless rope slings, each wire rope used in hoisting or lowering,
or bulling cargo, shall consist of one continuous piece without knot or splice. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Natural fibre rope.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) The employer shall ascertain and adhere to the manufacturer's recommended ratings for natural fibre rope and
natural fibre rope slings provided for use aboard ship, and shall have such ratings available for inspection. When
the manufacturer is unable to supply such ratings, Appendix II to this part provides guidelines for fibre rope ratings.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the manufacturers recommended ratings and use recommendations are unavailable, Table 2 of Appendix II to this
part provides guidelines to determine safe working loads of natural fibre rope slings comprising part of pre-slung
drafts. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Eye splices shall consist of at least three full tucks. Short splices shall consist of at least six tucks, three
on each side of the centerline. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Synthetic rope.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) The employer shall adhere to the manufacturer's ratings and use recommendations for the specific synthetic fibre
rope and synthetic fibre rope slings provided for use aboard ship, and shall have such ratings available for inspection.
When the manufacturer is unable to supply such ratings, the employer shall use Tables 3A and B of Appendix II to this
part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the manufacturers recommended ratings and use recommendations are unavailable, Tables 3A and B of Appendix
II to this part shall be used to determine the safe working load of synthetic fibre rope and of synthetic rope slings
comprising part of pre-slung drafts. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Unless otherwise recommended by the manufacturer, when synthetic fibre ropes are substituted for natural fibre
ropes of less than 3 inches (7.62 cm) in circumference, the substitute shall be of equal size. Where substituted for
natural fibre rope of 3 inches (7.62 cm) or more in circumference, the size of the synthetic rope shall be determined
from the formula:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->

<!-- PJG STAG 4725 -->

<IMPORT>

<!-- PJG importformat s,w86,d17 -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=92 g=1 f=1 -->
E:GRAPHICSEP02JN94.001
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

</IMPORT>

<!-- PJG /STAG -->

<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=16 g=1 f=1 -->
 Where C=the required circumference of the synthetic rope in inches (centimeters); C
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=16 g=5 f=2 -->
s
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=16 g=1 f=1 -->
= the circumference to the nearest one-quarter inch (.6 cm) of a synthetic rope having a breaking strength no less than
that of the size natural fibre rope that would be required by paragraph (c) of this section; and C
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=16 g=5 f=2 -->
m
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=16 g=1 f=1 -->
= the circumference of natural fibre rope in inches (centimeters) which would be required by paragraph (c) of this
section. In making each substitution, it shall be ascertained that the inherent characteristics of the synthetic-fibre
are suitable for hoisting. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Removal of natural and synthetic rope from service.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Natural and synthetic rope having any of the following defects shall be removed from service: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Abnormal or excessive wear including heat and chemical damage; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Powdered fibre between strands; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Sufficient cut or broken fibers to affect the capability of the rope; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
