<DOCNO> FR940602-1-00045 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940602-1-00013 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(4) Variations in the size or roundness of strands; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Discolorations other than stains not associated with rope damage; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Rotting; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Distortion or other damage to attached hardware. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Thimbles.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Properly fitting thimbles shall be used when any rope is secured permanently to a ring, shackle or attachment, where
practicable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Synthetic web slings.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Slings and nets or other combinations of more than one piece of synthetic webbing assembled and used as a single
unit (synthetic web slings) shall not be used to hoist loads in excess of the sling's rated capacity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Synthetic web slings shall be removed from service if they exhibit any of the following defects: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Acid or caustic burns; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Melting or charring of any part of the sling surface; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Snags, punctures, tears or cuts; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Broken or worn stitches; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Distortion or damage to fittings; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) Display of visible warning threads or markers designed to indicate excessive wear or damage. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Defective synthetic web slings removed from service shall not be returned to service unless repaired by a sling
manufacturer or an entity of similar competence. Each repaired sling shall be proof tested by the repairer to twice
the sling's rated capacity prior to its return to service. The employer shall retain a certificate of the proof test
and make it available for inspection. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Synthetic web slings provided by the employer shall only be used in accordance with the manufacturer's use recommendations,
which shall be available. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Fittings shall have a breaking strength at least equal to that of the sling to which they are attached and shall be
free of sharp edges. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Chains and chain slings used for hoisting.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) The employer shall adhere to the manufacturer's recommended ratings for safe working loads for the size of wrought
iron and alloy steel chains and chain slings and shall have such ratings available for inspection. When the manufacturer
does not provide such ratings, the employer shall use Table 4A of Appendix II to this part to determine safe working
loads for alloy steel chains and chain slings only. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Proof coil steel chain, also known as common or hardware chain, and other chain not recommended by the manufacturer
for slinging or hoisting, shall not be used for slinging or hoisting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) (i) Sling chains, including end fastenings, shall be inspected for visible defects before each day's use and as
often as necessary during use to ensure integrity of the sling. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Thorough inspections of chains in use shall be made quarterly to detect wear, defective welds, deformation or
increase in length or stretch. The month of inspection shall be indicated on each chain by color of paint on a link or
by other equally effective means. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Chains shall be removed from service when maximum allowable wear, as indicated in Table 4B of Appendix II to this
part, is reached at any point of a link. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Chain slings shall be removed from service when stretch has increased the length of a measured section by more
than five percent; when a link is bent, twisted or otherwise damaged; or when a link has a raised scarf or defective weld.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Only designated persons shall inspect chains used for slinging and hoisting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Chains shall only be repaired under qualified supervision. Links or portions of chain defective under any of the
criteria of paragraph (h)(3)(iv) of this section shall be replaced with properly dimensioned links or connections
of material similar to that of the original chain. Before repaired chains are returned to service, they shall be tested
to the proof test load recommended by the manufacturer for the original chain. Tests shall be performed by the manufacturer
or shall be certified by an agency accredited for the purpose under part 1919 of this chapter. Test certificates shall
be available for inspection. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) (i) Wrought iron chains in constant use shall be annealed or normalized at intervals not exceeding six months.
Heat treatment certificates shall be available for inspection. Alloy chains shall not be annealed. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) No new part of a lifting appliance or item of loose gear shall be manufactured of wrought iron. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Kinked or knotted chains shall not be used for lifting. Chains shall not be shortened by bolting, wiring or knotting.
Makeshift links or fasteners such as wire, bolts or rods shall not be used. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Hooks, rings, links and attachments affixed to sling chains shall have rated capacities at least equal to that
of the chains to which they are attached. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Chain slings shall bear identification of size, grade and rated capacity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Shackles.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) If available, the manufacturer's recommended safe working loads for shackles shall not be exceeded. In the absence
of the manufacturer's recommendations, Table 5 of Appendix II to this part, shall apply. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Screw pin shackles provided by the employer and used aloft, except in cargo hook assemblies, shall have their pins
positively secured. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(j) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Hooks other than hand hooks.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) The manufacturer's recommended safe working loads for hooks shall not be exceeded. Hooks other than hand hooks
shall be tested in accordance with the provisions of paragraphs (a), (c) and (d) of &sect;1919.31 of this chapter,
except, that manufacturer's test certificates indicating performance to the criteria in &sect;1919.31 (a), (c)
and (d) of this chapter shall be acceptable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Bent or sprung hooks shall be discarded. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Teeth of case hooks shall be maintained in safe condition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Jaws of patent clamp-type plate hooks shall be maintained in condition to grip plates securely. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Loads shall be applied to the throat of the hook only. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(k) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Pallets.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Pallets shall be made and maintained to support and carry loads being handled safely. Fastenings of reusable pallets
used for hoisting shall be bolts and nuts, drive screws (helically threaded nails), annular threaded nails or fastenings
of equivalent holding strength. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Reusable wing or lip-type pallets shall be hoisted by bar bridles or other suitable gear and shall have an overhanging
wing or lip of at least 3 inches (7.6 cm). They shall not be hoisted by wire slings alone. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Loaded pallets that do not meet the requirements of this paragraph shall be hoisted only after being placed on pallets
meeting such requirements, or shall be handled by other means providing equivalent safety. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Bridles for handling flush end or box-type pallets shall be designed to prevent disengagement from the pallet
under load. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940602-1-00046 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940602-1-00013 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(5) Pallets shall be stacked or placed to prevent falling, collapsing or otherwise causing a hazard under standard
operating conditions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Disposable pallets intended only for one use shall not be reused for hoisting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.63 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Chutes, gravity conveyors and rollers. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Chutes shall be of adequate length and strength to support the conditions of use, and shall be free of splinters
and sharp edges. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) When necessary for the safety of employees, chutes shall be equipped with sideboards to afford protection from
falling objects. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) When necessary for the safety of employees, provisions shall be made for stopping objects other than bulk commodities
at the delivery end of the chute. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Chutes and gravity conveyor roller sections shall be firmly placed and secured to prevent displacement, shifting,
or falling. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) Gravity conveyors shall be of sufficient strength to safely support the weight of materials placed upon them.
Conveyor rollers shall be installed in a manner that prevents them from falling or jumping out of the frame. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) Frames shall be kept free of burrs and sharp edges. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.64 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Powered conveyors. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Emergency stop.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Readily accessible stop controls shall be provided for use in an emergency. Whenever the operation of any power conveyor
requires personnel to work in the immediate vicinity of the conveyor, the conveyor controls shall not be left unattended
while the conveyor is in operation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Guarding.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 All conveyor and trimmer drives which create a hazard shall be adequately guarded. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Approved for location.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Electric motors and controls on conveyors and trimmers used to handle grain and exposed to grain dust shall be of the
type approved by a nationally recognized testing laboratory for use in Class II, Division I locations. (See &sect;1910.7
of this chapter.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Grain trimmer control box.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Each grain trimmer shall have a control box located on the weather deck in close proximity to the spout feeding the trimmer.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Grain trimmer power cable.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Power cables between the deck control box and the grain trimmer shall be used only in continuous lengths without splice
or tap between connections. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Portable conveyors.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Portable conveyors shall be stable within their operating ranges. When used at variable fixed levels, the unit shall
be secured at the operating level. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Delivery and braking.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 When necessary for the safety of employees, provisions shall be made for braking objects at the delivery end of the
conveyor. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Electric brakes.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Conveyors using electrically released brakes shall be so constructed that the brakes cannot be released until power
is applied, and that the brakes are automatically engaged if the power fails or the operating control is returned to
the ``stop'' position. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Starting powered conveyors.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Powered conveyors shall not be started until all employees are clear of the conveyor or have been warned that the conveyor
is about to start. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(j) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Loading and unloading.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The area around conveyor loading and unloading points shall be kept clear of obstructions during conveyor operations.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(k) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Lockout/tagout.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Conveyors shall be stopped and their power sources locked out and tagged out during maintenance, repair, and servicing,
unless power is necessary for testing or for making minor adjustments. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The starting device shall be locked out and tagged out in the stop position before an attempt is made to remove the
cause of a jam or overload of the conveying medium. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(l) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Safe practices.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Only designated persons shall operate, repair or service powered conveyors. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The employer shall direct employees to stay off operating conveyors. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Conveyors shall be operated only with all overload devices, guards and safety devices in place and operable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.65 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Mechanically powered vehicles used aboard vessels. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicability.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This section applies to every type of mechanically powered vehicle used for material or equipment handling aboard
a vessel. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940602-1-00047 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940602-1-00013 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Modifications, such as adding counterweights that might affect the vehicle's capacity or safety, shall not be
performed without either the manufacturer's prior written approval or the written approval of a professional engineer
experienced with the equipment, who has consulted with the manufacturer, if available. Capacity, operation and
maintenance instruction plates, tags or decals shall be changed to conform to the equipment as modified.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Rated capacities, with and without removable counterweights, shall not be exceeded. Rated capacities shall
be marked on the vehicle and shall be visible to the operator. The vehicle weight, with and without counterweight,
shall be similarly marked. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If loads are lifted by two or more trucks working in unison, the total weight shall not exceed the combined safe lifting
capacity of all trucks. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Guards for fork lift trucks. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Except as noted in paragraph (c)(5) of this section, fork lift trucks shall be equipped with overhead guards securely
attached to the machines. The guard shall be of such design and construction as to protect the operator from boxes,
cartons, packages, bagged material, and other similar individual items of cargo which may fall from the load being
handled or from stowage. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Overhead guards shall not obstruct the operator's view, and openings in the top of the guard shall not exceed 6 inches
(15.2 cm) in one of the two directions, width or length. Larger openings are permitted if no opening allows the smallest
unit of cargo being handled through the guard.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Overhead guards shall be built so that failure of the vehicle's mast tilting mechanism will not displace the guard.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Overhead guards shall be large enough to extend over the operator during all truck operations, including forward
tilt.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) An overhead guard may be removed only when it would prevent a truck from entering a work space and if the operator
is not exposed to low overhead obstructions in the work space. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Where necessary to protect the operator, fork lift trucks shall be fitted with a vertical load backrest extension
to prevent the load from hitting the mast when the mast is positioned at maximum backward tilt. For this purpose, a ``load
backrest extension'' means a device extending vertically from the fork carriage frame to prevent raised loads from
falling backward. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Guards for bulk cargo-moving vehicles. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Every crawler type, rider operated, bulk cargo-moving vehicle shall be equipped with an operator's guard of such
design and construction as to protect the operator, when seated, against injury from contact with a projecting overhead.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Guards and their attachment points shall be so designed as to be able to withstand, without excessive deflection,
a load applied horizontally at the operator's shoulder level equal to the drawbar pull of the machine.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Guards shall not be required when the vehicle is used in situations in which the possibility of the seated operator
coming in contact with projecting overheads does not exist.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Bulk cargo-moving vehicles shall be equipped with roll-over protection of such design and construction as to
minimize the possibility of the operator being crushed as a result of a roll-over or upset.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Approved vehicle. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) ``Approved power-operated vehicle'' means one listed as approved for the intended use or location by a nationally
recognized testing laboratory.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Approved vehicles shall bear a label or other identification indicating testing laboratory approval.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) When the atmosphere in an area is hazardous and the provisions of U.S. Coast Guard regulations 49 CFR 176.78 do not
apply, only approved power-operated vehicles shall be used.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Maintenance. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Mechanically powered vehicles shall be maintained in safe working order. Safety devices shall not be removed
or made inoperative except as otherwise provided in this section. Vehicles with a fuel system leak or any other safety
defect shall not be operated.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Braking systems or other mechanisms used for braking shall be operable and in safe condition.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Replacement parts whose function might affect operational safety shall be equivalent in strength and performance
capability to the original parts which they replace.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Repairs to the fuel and ignition systems of mechanically powered vehicles which involve fire hazards shall be
conducted only in locations designated as safe for such repairs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Batteries on all mechanically powered vehicles shall be disconnected during repairs to the primary electrical
system unless power is necessary for testing and repair. On vehicles equipped with systems capable of storing residual
energy, that energy shall be safely discharged before work on the primary electrical system begins. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Only designated persons shall perform maintenance and repair.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Parking brakes. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
All mechanically powered vehicles purchased after [insert effective date of the Final Rule] shall be equipped with
parking brakes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Operation. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Only stable and safely arranged loads within the rated capacity of the mechanically powered vehicle shall be handled.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The employer shall direct drivers to ascend and descend grades slowly.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If the load obstructs the forward view, the employer shall direct drivers to travel with the load trailing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Steering knobs shall not be used unless the vehicle is equipped with power steering. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) When mechanically powered vehicles use cargo lifting devices that have a means of engagement hidden from the operator,
a means shall be provided to enable the operator to determine that the cargo has been engaged.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
