<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(6) No load on a mechanically powered vehicle shall be suspended or swung over any employee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) When mechanically powered vehicles are used, provisions shall be made to ensure that the working surface can support
the vehicle and load, and that hatch covers, truck plates, or other temporary surfaces cannot be dislodged by movement
of the vehicle.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) When mechanically powered vehicles are left unattended, load-engaging means shall be fully lowered, controls
neutralized, brakes set and power shut off. Wheels shall be blocked or curbed if the vehicle is on an incline.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) When lift trucks or other mechanically powered vehicles are being operated on open deck type barges, the edges
of the barges shall be guarded by railings, sideboards, timbers, or other means sufficient to prevent vehicles from
rolling overboard. When such vehicles are operated on covered lighters where door openings other than those being
used are left open, means shall be taken to prevent vehicles from rolling overboard through such openings.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) Unauthorized personnel shall not ride on mechanically powered vehicles. A safe place to ride shall be provided
when riding is authorized.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) An employee may be elevated by fork lift trucks only when a platform is secured to the lifting carriage or forks.
The platform shall meet the following requirements:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The platform shall have a railing complying with &sect;1917.112(c) of this chapter.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The platform shall have toeboards complying with &sect;1917.112(d) of this chapter, if tools or other objects
could fall on employees below.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) When the truck has controls which are elevated with the lifting carriage, means shall be provided for employees
on the platform to shut off power to the vehicle.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Employees on the platform shall be protected from exposure to moving truck parts.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) The platform floor shall be skid resistant.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) A truck operator shall be at the truck's controls when employees are elevated, unless the truck's controls are
elevated with the lifting carriage.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) While an employee is elevated the truck may be moved only to make minor placement adjustments.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.66
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Cranes and derricks other than vessel's gear.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The following requirements shall apply to the use of cranes and derricks brought aboard vessels for the purpose of
conducting longshoring operations. They shall not apply to cranes and derricks forming part of a vessels permanent
equipment.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(l) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Certification. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Cranes and derricks shall be certificated in accordance with part 1919 of this chapter.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Posted weight. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The crane weight shall be posted on all cranes hoisted aboard vessels for temporary use.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Rating chart. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
All cranes and derricks having ratings that vary with boom length, radius (outreach) or other variables shall have
a durable rating chart visible to the operator, covering the complete range of the manufacturer's (or design) capacity
ratings. The rating chart shall include all operating radii (outreach) for all permissible boom lengths and jib lengths,
as applicable, with and without outriggers, and alternate ratings for optional equipment affecting such ratings.
Precautions or warnings specified by the owner or manufacturer shall be included along with a chart.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Rated loads. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The manufacturer's (or design) rated loads for the conditions of use shall not be exceeded.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Change of rated loads. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Designated working loads shall not be increased beyond the manufacturer's ratings or original design limitations
unless such increase receives the manufacturer's approval. When the manufacturer's services are not available
or where the equipment is of foreign manufacture, engineering design analysis shall be performed or approved by a
person accredited for certificating the equipment under part 1919 of this chapter. Engineering design analysis
shall be performed by a registered professional engineer competent in the field of cranes and derricks. Any structural
changes necessitated by the change in rating shall be carried out.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Radius indicator. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
When the rated load varies with the boom radius, the crane or derrick shall be fitted with a boom angle or radius indicator
visible to the operator.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
