<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(7) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Operator's station. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The cab, controls and mechanism of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the equipment shall be so arranged that the operator has a clear 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
view of the load or signalman, when one is used. Cab glass, when 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
used, shall be safety plate glass or equivalent and good 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
visibility shall be maintained through the glass. Clothing, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
tools, and equipment shall be stored so as not to interfere with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
access, operation, and the operator's view. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Counterweights or ballast. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Cranes shall be operated 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
only with the specified type and amount of ballast or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
counterweights. Ballast or counterweights shall be located and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
secured only as provided in the manufacturer's or design 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
specifications, which shall be available for inspection. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Outriggers. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Outriggers shall be used according to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
manufacturer's specifications or design data, which shall be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
available for inspection. Floats, when used, shall be securely 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
attached to the outriggers. Wood blocks or other support shall 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be of sufficient size to support the outrigger, free of defects 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that may affect safety and of sufficient width and length to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
prevent the crane from shifting or toppling under load. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Exhaust gases. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Engine exhaust gases shall be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
discharged away from the normal position of crane operating 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
personnel. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Electrical/Guarding. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Electrical equipment shall be so 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
located or enclosed that live parts will not be exposed to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accidental contact. Designated persons may work on energized 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
equipment only if necessary during inspection, maintenance, or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
repair, otherwise the equipment shall be stopped and their power 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sources locked out and tagged out. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fire extinguisher. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(i) At least one portable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approved or listed fire extinguisher of at least a 5&hyph;BC rating or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
equivalent shall be accessible in the cab of the crane or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
derrick. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) No portable fire extinguisher using carbon 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
tetrachloride or chlorobromomethane extinguishing agents shall be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
used. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(13) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Rope on drums. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
At least three full turns of rope 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall remain on ungrooved drums, and two turns on grooved drums, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under all operating conditions. Wire rope shall be secured to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
drums by clamps, U-bolts, shackles or equivalent means. Fibre 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rope fastenings are prohibited. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(14) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Brakes. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(i) Each independent hoisting unit of a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
crane shall be equipped with at least one holding brake, applied 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
directly to the motor shaft or gear train. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Each independent hoisting unit of a crane shall, in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
addition to the holding brake, be equipped with a controlled 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
braking means to control lowering speeds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Holding brakes for hoist units shall have not less 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
than the following percentage of the rated load hoisting torque 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
at the point where the brake is applied: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) 125 percent when used with a controlled braking means. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) 100 percent when used with a mechanically controlled 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
braking means. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) All power control braking means shall be capable of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
maintaining safe lowering speeds of rated loads. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(15) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Operating controls. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Crane and derrick operating 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
controls shall be clearly marked, or a chart indicating their 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
function shall be posted at the operator's position. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(16) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Booms. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Cranes with elevatable booms and without 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
operable automatic limiting devices shall be provided with boom 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
stops if boom elevation can exceed maximum design angles from the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
horizontal. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(17) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Foot pedals. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Foot pedals shall have a non-skid 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
surface. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(18) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Access. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Ladders, stairways, stanchions, grab irons, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
foot steps or equivalent means shall be provided as necessary to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ensure safe access to footwalks, cab platforms, the cab and any 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
portion of the superstructure which employees must reach. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Operations_(1) Use of cranes together. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
When two or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
more cranes hoist a load in unison, a designated person shall 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
direct the operation and instruct personnel in positioning, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rigging of the load and movements to be made. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Guarding of swing radius. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Accessible areas within the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
swing radius of the body of a revolving crane shall be physically 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
guarded during operations to prevent an employee from being 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
caught between the body of the crane and any fixed structure or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
between parts of the crane. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
