<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940602-1-00054 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940602-1-00013 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(B) Employees engaged in work on containers that are not being handled by container gantry cranes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Compliance with paragraph (j)(1)(ii) of this section shall be considered feasible when containers are being
worked by container gantry cranes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Where the employer determines in the particular case that an employee will be exposed to a fall hazard but that the
use of a fall protection system meeting the requirements of paragraph (k) of this section is not feasible
<FOOTCITE>5</FOOTCITE>
 the employer shall alert the exposed employee about the hazards involved and instruct the employee how to minimize
the hazard. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<FOOTNOTE>
<FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
5
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

</FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
See non-mandatory Appendix III to this part for examples of situations where the use of a fall protection system may
prove infeasible. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
</FOOTNOTE>

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(k) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fall protection. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
When fall protection systems required by paragraph (j) of this section are employed, the following shall apply: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Each fall protection system component, except anchorages, shall have fall arrest/restraint as its only use.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Each fall protection system subjected to impact loading shall be immediately withdrawn from service and not used
again until inspected and determined by a designated person to be undamaged and suitable for use. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Each fall protection system shall be rigged to minimize free-fall distance so that the employee will not contact
any lower level stowage or vessel structure. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Each fall protection system adopted for use shall have an energy absorbing mechanism that will produce an arresting
force on an employee of not greater than 1800 pounds (8 kN). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Each fall protection systems' hardware shall be designed and utilized so as to prevent accidental disengagement.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Each fall protection systems' fixed anchorages shall each be capable of sustaining a force of 5,000 (22.2 kN) pounds
or be certified as capable of sustaining at least twice the potential impact load of an employee's fall. Such certification
must be made by a registered professional engineer. When more than one employee is attached to an anchorage, the foregoing
limits shall be multiplied by the number of employees attached. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) When ``live'' (activated) container gantry crane lifting beams or attached devices are used as anchorage points
the following requirements apply: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The crane shall be placed into a ``slow'' speed mode; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The crane shall be equipped with a remote shut-off switch, capable of stopping all crane functions, in the control
of employee(s) attached to the beam; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A visible or audible indicator shall be present to inform the same employee(s) when the remote shut-off is operational.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Fall protection system components shall be certified as a unit of being capable of sustaining at least twice the
potential impact load of an employee's fall. Such certification must be made by a registered professional engineer.
When more than one employee is attached to an anchorage, the foregoing limits shall be multiplied by the number of employees
attached. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) Each fall protection system shall incorporate the use of a full body harnesses. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) Each device, such as a safety cage, that is used to transport employee(s) by being attached to a container gantry
crane spreader, shall have a secondary means of attachment in place and engaged to prevent accidental disengagement.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) Each fall protection system shall be inspected prior to each day's use by a designated person. Any defective components
shall be removed from service. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) Before using any fall protection system, the employee shall be trained in the use and application limits of the
equipment, proper hook-up, anchoring and tie-off techniques, methods of use, and proper methods of equipment inspection
and storage. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(13) The employer shall establish and implement a procedure to safely retrieve personnel in case of a fall. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(l) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Working along unguarded edges. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Fall protection meeting the requirements of paragraph (k) of this section must be provided when container operations
require employees to work along unguarded edges (other than on the top of a container), where the fall distance is greater
than 8 feet (2.4 m). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.86 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Roll-on roll-off (RO-RO) operations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(See also &sect;1918.24.) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
