<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Traffic control system.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 An organized system of vehicular and pedestrian traffic control shall be established and maintained at each entrance/exit
ramp and on ramps within the vessel as traffic flow warrants. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Ramp load limit.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Ramps shall be plainly marked with their load capacity. The marked capacity shall not be exceeded. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Pedestrian traffic.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Stern and side port ramps also used for pedestrian access shall meet the requirements of &sect;1918.21. Such ramps
shall provide a physical separation between pedestrian and vehicular routes. When the design of the ramp prevents
physical separation, a signalperson shall direct traffic and shall not allow concurrent use. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Ramp maintenance.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Ramps shall be properly maintained and secured. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Hazardous routes.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Prior to the start of Ro-Ro operations the employer shall ascertain any hazardous routes or areas that could be mistaken
for normal drive-on/drive-off routes. Such hazardous routes shall be clearly identified and barricaded. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Air brake connections.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Each tractor shall have all air lines connected when pulling trailers equipped with air brakes and shall have the brakes
tested before commencing operations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Trailer load limits.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Flat bed and low boy trailers shall be marked with their cargo capacities and shall not be overloaded. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Cargo weights.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Cargo to be handled via a Ro-Ro ramp shall have its weight plainly marked in pounds (kilograms). Alternatively, the
cargo stow plan or equivalent record containing the actual gross weight of the load may be used to determine the weight
of the cargo. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Tractors.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Tractors used in Ro-Ro operations shall have: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) sufficient power to ascend ramp inclines safely; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) sufficient braking capacity to descend ramp inclines safely. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(j) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Safe speeds.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Power driven vehicles used in Ro-Ro operations shall be operated at safe speeds compatible with prevailing conditions.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(k) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Ventilation.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Internal combustion engine driven vehicles shall be operated only where adequate ventilation exists or is provided.
(Air contaminant requirements are found in &sect;1918.94 and part 1910, subpart Z of this chapter.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(l) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Securing cargo.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Cargo loaded or discharged during Ro-Ro operations shall be secured to prevent sliding loads. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(m) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Authorized personnel.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Only authorized persons shall be permitted on any deck while loading or discharging operations are being conducted.
Such authorized persons shall be equipped with high visibility vests (or equivalent protection). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(n) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Signalling requirement.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 When a driver is maneuvering a vehicle into a stowage position while other personnel, such as lashers, are working
in the adjacent vicinity: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) the driver shall be under the direction of a signaller; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) No driver shall be signalled to advance or reverse motion while any personnel are in positions where they could
be struck. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.87 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Ship's cargo elevators. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Safe working load.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The safe working loads of ship's cargo elevators shall be ascertained and adhered to. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Load distribution.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Loads shall be evenly distributed on the elevator's platform. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Elevator personnel restrictions.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Drivers of vehicles who remain at the controls of those vehicles shall be the only persons permitted to travel on the
elevator's platform with the vehicle. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Open deck barricades.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 During elevator operation, each opened deck which presents a fall hazard to employees shall be effectively barricaded.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.88 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Log operations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(See also &sect;1918.38.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Working in holds.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 In holds where logs are being loaded, no employee shall remain in spaces for the placement of logs using dumper devices
when the possibility of logs striking, rolling upon, or pinning them exists. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Footwear.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The employer shall provide employees that are working logs appropriate footwear, such as spiked shoes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
