<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
First aid kit.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 First aid kits shall be weatherproof and shall contain individual sealed packages for each item that must be kept sterile.
The contents of each kit shall be determined by a physician, based on the hazards anticipated at the worksite. The contents
of the first aid kit shall be checked at least weekly. Expended items shall be promptly replaced. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Stretchers.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) There shall be available for each vessel being worked, one Stokes basket stretcher, or its equivalent, permanently
equipped with bridles for attaching to the hoisting gear. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Stretchers shall be kept close to vessels and shall be positioned to avoid damage. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) A blanket or other suitable covering shall be available. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Stretchers shall have at least four sets of effective patient restraints in operable condition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Lifting bridles shall be of adequate strength, capable of lifting 1,000 pounds (454 kg) with a safety factor of
five, and shall be maintained in operable condition. Lifting bridles shall be provided for making vertical patient
lifts at container berths. Stretchers for vertical lifts shall have foot plates. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Stretchers shall be maintained in operable condition. Struts and braces shall be inspected for damage. Wire mesh
shall be secured with no burrs. Damaged stretchers shall not be used until repaired. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Life-rings.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) The employer shall ensure that there is in the vicinity of each vessel being worked, at least one U.S. Coast Guard
approved 30 inch (76.2 cm) life-ring with no less than 90 feet (27.4 m) of line attached and at least one portable or permanent
ladder which will reach from the top of the apron to the surface of the water.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) In addition to the provisions of paragraph (e) of this section, when working a barge, scow, raft, lighter, log boom,
or carfloat alongside a ship, a U.S. Coast Guard approved 30 inch (76.2 cm) life-ring, with no less than 90 feet (27.4
m) of line shall be provided either on the floating unit itself or aboard the ship in the immediate vicinity of each floating
unit being worked. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Communication.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Telephone or equivalent means of communication shall be readily available. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1918.98 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Personnel. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Qualification of machinery operators.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Only those employees determined by the employer to be competent by reason of training or experience, and who understand
the signs, notices and operating instructions, and are familiar with the signal code in use, shall be permitted to
operate a crane, winch, or other power operated cargo handling apparatus, or any power operated vehicle, or give signals
to the operator of any hoisting apparatus. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
However, employees being trained and supervised by a designated person may operate such machinery and give signals
to operators during training. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) No employee known to have defective uncorrected eyesight or hearing, or to be suffering from heart disease, epilepsy,
or similar ailments which may suddenly incapacitate the employee, shall be permitted to operate a crane, winch or
other power operated cargo handling apparatus or a power-operated 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
vehicle. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Supervisory accident prevention proficiency.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) After [insert date two years after promulgation of final standard], immediate supervisors of cargo handling
operations of more than five persons shall satisfactorily complete a course in accident prevention. Employees newly
assigned to supervisory duties after that date shall be required to meet the provisions of this paragraph within 90
days of such assignment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The accident prevention course shall consist of instruction suited to the particular operations involved.
