(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Protective clothing.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) The employer shall provide, and shall require the wearing of special protective clothing for those employees
engaged in work in which such protective clothing is necessary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) When necessary, protective clothing shall be cleaned and disinfected before reissuance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Personal flotation equipment.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) The employer shall provide, and shall require the wearing of personal flotation devices for those employees engaged
in work in which they may fall into the water: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) When such employees are working in isolation; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Where physical limitations of available working space creates a hazard of falling into the water; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Where the work area is obstructed by cargo or other obstacles so as to prevent employees from obtaining safe footing
for their work; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) When working on the deck of a barge. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Personal flotation devices shall be United States Coast Guard approved Type I PFD, Type II PFD, Type III PFD, or
Type V PFD, or equivalent, in accordance with 46 CFR part 160 (Coast Guard Lifesaving Equipment Specifications) and
33 CFR part 175.23 (Coast Guard table of devices equivalent to personal flotation devices). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Personal flotation devices shall be maintained in safe condition and shall be considered unserviceable when
damaged so as to affect buoyancy or fastening capability. 
