<!-- PJG ITAG l=73 g=1 f=1 -->
General 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
The tests, examinations and inspections indicated in this register are based on the requirements of I.L.O. Convention
152 and Recommendation 160. They are intended to ensure that ships having lifting appliances are initially certified
by a competent person, and to establish periodically that they continue to be in safe working order to the satisfaction
of a competent person 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
acceptable to a competent authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
A Register of lifting appliances and items of loose gear shall be kept in a form prescribed by the competent authority,
account being taken of this model recommended by the International Labour Office. This Register and related certificates
shall be kept available to any person authorized by the competent authority. The Register and certificates for gear
currently aboard the ship shall be preserved for at least five years after the date of the last entry. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=73 g=1 f=1 -->
Instruction 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=71 g=1 f=1 -->
1. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=71 g=1 f=3 -->
Initial Examination and Certification 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=3 -->
1.1. Every lifting appliance shall be certified by a competent person before being taken into use for the first time
to ensure that it is of good design and construction and of adequate strength for the purpose for which it is intended.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1.2. Before being taken into use for the first time, a competent person shall supervise and witness testing, and shall
thoroughly examine every lifting appliance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1.3. Every item of loose gear shall, before being taken into use for the first time, shall be tested, thoroughly examined
and certified by a competent person, in accordance with national law or regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1.4. Upon satisfactory completion of the procedures indicated above, the competent person shall complete and issue
the Register of lifting appliances and attach the appropriate certificates. An entry shall be made in part I of the
Register. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1.5. A rigging plan showing the arrangement of lifting appliances shall be provided. In the case of derricks and derrick
cranes, the rigging should show at least the following information. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) the position of guys; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) the resultant force on blocks, guys, wire ropes and booms; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) the position of blocks; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) the identification mark of individual items; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) arrangements and working range of union purchase; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=71 g=1 f=3 -->
2. Periodic Examination and Re-testing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=3 -->
2.1. All lifting appliances and every item of loose gear shall be thoroughly examined by a competent person at least
once in every twelve months. The particulars of these thorough examinations shall be entered in part I of the Register.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2.2. Re-testing and thorough examination of all lifting appliances and every item of loose gear is to be carried out;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) after any substantial alteration or renewal, or after repair to any stress bearing part, and; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) in the case of lifting appliances, at least once in every five years. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2.3. The retesting referred to in paragraph 2.2(a) may be omitted provided the part which has been renewed or repaired
is subjected by separate test, to the same stress as would be imposed on it if it had been tested in-situ during the testing
of the lifting appliance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2.4. The thorough examinations and tests referred to in paragraph 2.2. are to be entered in part I of the Register. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
