<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
B. Requirements Regarding the Trial Burn 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
1. Notices of Trial Burns
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In section 4.c: Notices of Trial Burns, EPA is requesting comments on whether the permitting authority or the facility
should be responsible for providing public notices during the trial burn stage. EPA is also requesting comments,
in section 5.c.2: Interim Status Combustion Facilities, on whether the Agency should establish a comment period
for interim status facilities prior to approving the trial burn plan, in view of the fact that, for permitted facilities,
the public has an opportunity to comment on a draft trial burn plan as part of the draft permit process. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

